This should work as expected. To implement a 'stoppable' thread-like version, maybe consider:

```python
class _Foo:
    def __init__(self):
        self._callback = []
        # Store all callable events

    def after(self, time, function_to_call):
        """Call `function_to_call` after `time` milliseconds."""
        self.tk.after(time, function_to_call)

    def every(self, time, function_to_call):
        """Call `function_to_call` every `time` milliseconds."""
        self._callback[function_to_call] = True
        def _call_wrapper():
            if self._callback[function_to_call]:
                function_to_call()
                self.tk.after(time, _call_wrapper)
            else:
                return
        self.tk.after(time, _call_wrapper)

    def cancel(self, function_to_call):
        """Cancel the scheduled `function_to_call`."""
        self._callback[function_to_call] = False
```

This is making the assumption that `every` calls will have unique `function_to_call` arguments. Some other things that caught my attention:

* `tk.after` expects milliseconds, so why are you converting `time` to seconds?
* Maybe rename `every` to `schedule` or `repeat`?

The fact that anonymous downloads work at least means that the extractor itself is working and the issue is most likely tied to your account or your internet connection.

You also didn't provide your cookies in a way that gallery-dl can access them, as it doesn't fall back to anonymous mode if these two values are present. Make sure that this part in your config file looks something like this:
```
{
  "extractor": {
    "exhentai": {
      "cookies": {
        "ipb_member_id": "<your id>",
        "ipb_pass_hash": "<your password hash>"
      }
    }
  }
}
 ```

Another thing that you could try out would be to run the extractor test for `exhentai`: navigate to the [`test` directory](https://github.com/mikf/gallery-dl/tree/master/test), run
`$ python3 test_extractors.py exhentai`
and post the output here.

I'm really not sure why it doesn't work for you, so all of these methods are just there to narrow down the problem and find the actual "culprit". Maybe you are using a VPN or proxy that is causing issues, or your account is too young ... but you said that it is working in your browser, so this couldn't be it either ...

