For what's worth, what's causing the issue is the many calls to `import_array()` inside the constructors. My understanding from [this thread](https://mail.scipy.org/pipermail/numpy-discussion/2010-December/054345.html) is that `import_array()` should be called only from the module initialization function, and nowhere else. Specifically, the way this runs into trouble in HMpTY is that in python3 `import_array()` returns a value, and you can't return a value from a constructor.

It seems, in addition, that HMpTy uses SWIG. In that case, it seems (from reading [this](htmc.i)) that the simplest way to fix it is to add the following:

```
%init %{
import_array();
%}
```

to `htmc.i`.

