I forgot to update this thread, but Python 3 is supported since 7a490e07f802cf33200a4c8254c6025a804696fe that was released as version 1.2rc of ARC and can be found  [here](https://github.com/nikolasibalic/ARC-Alkali-Rydberg-Calculator/releases/tag/1.2rc). The pickle problem, turned out to be actually `numpy.load` problem, which wouldn't work before I defined flag `encoding="latin1"`.

Underlying cause is that Python 3 by default assumes `utf-8` encoding, while Python 2 uses `ascii` (see more [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38316283/trouble-using-numpy-load) ).

