@perrygreenfield wrote:
> To make sure I got that right.

I think you got it.  Each number in the lists is a group number.  Any inputs with the same number would give the outputs of the same number independent of the other inputs.  As further example for clarification: ([0, 1, 2, 3], [0, 1, 2, 3]) is completely separable, ([0, 0, 0, 0], [0, 0, 0, 0]) is completely unseparable.

