Thank you @SergeyKanzhelev. I don't have the time to add the operation logic to the WSGIApp at the moment, but hopefully I can the future.

For those who are in a similar position, I have added logic to our internal Python telemetry module to inject the 'X-Ms-Request-Id' header into any telemetry events where the Flask context exists. 

It's a mitigation, but we can now correlate our telemetry events across NodeJS and Python services using a query that looks for operationId in the App Insights column and within customDimensions.

```
from Flask import request, has_request_context
def add_correlation_id(self):
        telemetry_dimensions['operation_Id'] = 'Not-Set'
        if has_request_context():
            try:
                if request.headers is not None:
                    if 'X-Ms-Request-Id' in request.headers:
                        # Populate customDimensions with value from header. Doesn't perform the full operationId/parentOperationID data model defined for App Insights.
                        telemetry_dimensions['operation_Id'] = request.headers['X-Ms-Request-Id']
            # Catches error when there is no Flask context
            except AttributeError:
                pass
```

