if num_sessions > 100:
      train, valid = split()
     # just split. Verifying will be probably quite slow
```

Turns out that somebody added `implements AutoCloseable` to the Context class, which has the effect that the those objects are never freed in your example. Instead, you have to manually call `ctx.close()` when you don't need it anymore, or you use them in try-with style like so:

```
try (Context c = new Context(new HashMap<>())) {
  // ...
}
```

I guess I'll have to re-add some finalization function to make sure Contexts get deleted.

