One thing to note is that if you are going to have a lot of variant forms of roughly the same thing, for explicit dispatch I have written a [library called variants](https://github.com/python-variants/variants) that provides some syntactic sugar for adding variant methods.

Unfortunately it [does not currently work with classmethods](https://github.com/python-variants/variants/issues/1), but that's definitely coming (plus there are other ways to implement the same general concept without the variants library that *will* work with classmethods). [Here are the slides](https://pganssle.github.io/lightning-talks/python-variants/#/) for a lightning talk I gave about this, if you are interested.

